        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> If you are in Iceclad you are only a zone away from some great experience.  Head to Eastern Wastes and kill walrus.  You can find a great camp in the southwest corner of the zone near the Kael entrance.  </P><P>For safest traveling when you get to the end of the bridge from Iceclad just hang a left and follow the coast.  Takes awhile to get there but you can't miss it when you do.  </P><P>You can pull the walrus back to the east just a bit from their spawning ground to an open area on the coast.  This area is good for root cooking or fear kiting.  There are no adds and the fear pathing is excellent.  I preferred root cooking myself and went with the following line up.</P><P>1)Dooming Darkness<BR>2)VoS<BR>3)Boil Blood<BR>4)Vamp Curse<BR>5)Lifetap<BR>6)Root<BR>7)Feign Death<BR>8)Call of Bones</P><P>I personally am not overwhelmed by the benefits of the OT club especially with the ability to once again bind in the Firepot room.  Hunting in EW will give you as good if not better xp than OT and you won't ruin your faction with Chardok. As an added bonus killing walrus will raise your faction with Othmir.  Not a big deal but it may prove useful if you are going to do a lot of hunting in Cobalt Scar later on. </P><P>I did 34-39 here and all the walrus were still dark blue when I left and it was not rare to see even cons and rarely a yellow one.  If you stay into your 40s you could also hunt the ulthork that spawn there and perhaps get the tusks for the gem quest in Cobalt Scar. </P><P></P><P><BR> </font></td>
